B & friends:
	hacked up version of bcvi and related tools which works on
	top of sshfs so that I can always use MacVim as my editor

fixdate
	Usage: /Users/tadhunt/Documents/Personal/src/tools/bin/sh/fixdate YYYY-MM-DD[:[-]HH[:[-]mm[:[-]ss]]] [files]...
		Changes the date on [files]... to the provided date.
		Where YYYY is the new year, MM is the new month, and DD is the new day
		If HH is specified, it is added to the original hour
		If mm is specified, it is added to the original minutes
		If ss is specified, it is added to the original seconds
